value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine + L-homocysteine = cystathionine + H2O.

Catalysis of the reaction: L-seryl-tRNA(Sec) + selenophosphate = L-selenocysteinyl-tRNA(Sec) + H2O + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + (d)CMP = ADP + (d)CDP.

label.value: cytochrome-b5 reductase activity, acting on NAD(P)H

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)H + H+ + 2 ferricytochrome b(5) = NAD(P)+ + 2 ferrocytochrome b(5).
Catalysis of the reaction: 4 ferrocytochrome c + O2 + 4 H+ = 4 ferricytochrome c + 2 H2O.

definition.value: The reduction of O2 to water is accompanied by the extrusion of four protons from the intramitochondrial compartment.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 ferrocytochrome c + hydrogen peroxide = 2 ferricytochrome c + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: cytosine + H2O = uracil + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction: dCMP + H2O = dUMP + NH3.
Catalysis of the cleavage of branch points in branched glycogen polymers.
Catalysis of the transfer of a segment of a (1->4)-alpha-D-glucan to a new 4-position in an acceptor, which may be glucose or (1->4)-alpha-D-glucan.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->6)-alpha-D-glucosidic branch linkages in glycogen phosphorylase limit dextrin. Limit dextrin is the highly branched core that remains after exhaustive treatment of glycogen with glycogen phosphorylase. It is formed because these enzymes cannot hydrolyze the (1->6) glycosidic linkages present.

definition.value: Note that this is the first step in the formation of farnesyl diphosphate. The second step is 'geranyltranstransferase activity ; GO:0004337'. Consider also annotating to the biological process term 'farnesyl diphosphate biosynthetic process ; GO:0045337'.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-5-diphosphomevalonate + ATP = ADP + CO2 + H+ + isopentenyl diphosphate + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: 2-[(3S)-amino-3-carboxypropyl]-L-histidyl-[translation elongation factor 2] + 3 S-adenosyl-L-methionine = diphthine-[translation elongation factor 2] + 3 H+ + 3 S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.

definition.value: This activity is present in archae and produces the trimethylated product diphthine, which is converted into diphthamide by diphthine-ammonia ligase activity ; GO:0017178 (EC:6.3.1.14). Note that this is different from the eukaryotic enzyme diphthine methyl ester synthase activity ; GO:0141133 (EC:2.1.1.314), which produces diphthine methyl ester.

definition.value: Note that this activity has never been observed in green plants. However, N- and C-mannosylation may occur in these species; see figure 1 in PMID:21558543.
